INSERT INTO `Report` VALUES ('03cecddc-ed16-4480-839c-f9bde4b781ed','Completion Report for Amis de la Paix and Engineer for Humanity Web Platforms','\"\\\"<h3><br></h3><p>After a detailed review and completion phase, the Amis de la Paix website and the Engineer for Humanity website have reached their final operational state. All required configurations, layouts, and system checks have been completed, ensuring smooth performance and stability.</p><p>The websites are now live and functioning as intended. There are no outstanding technical issues or unfinished components. What remains is the responsibility of providing accurate and real data, such as finalized text, official records, and validated organizational details.</p><h3><br></h3><p>Both websites are complete and ready for deployment. Once real data is added, they can immediately be used as official digital platforms for their respective organizations.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-29 14:46:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('03d5257a-bc07-4622-90ca-7d2f8457069a','Aby Dash – Stock Fix & Order Update Report','\"\\\"<h1><strong>Aby Dash – Stock Fix &amp; Order Update Report</strong></h1><p><strong>Name: </strong>Ishimwe Serge</p><p><br></p><p>? <strong>Introduction</strong></p><p>Today, I completed important updates on the Aby Dash system focused on fixing stock-related issues and improving how client orders are managed. The goal was to ensure accurate stock tracking and make the ordering process smoother and more efficient.</p><p>✅ <strong>Key Tasks Completed</strong></p><p>? <strong>1. Fixed Stock Calculation Issues</strong></p><p>Identified and resolved inconsistencies in stock quantity updates.</p><p> Ensured that adding, removing, or modifying items correctly adjusts stock levels.</p><p> Improved the reliability of the stock management system for daily use.</p><p>? <strong>2. Added Logic to Attach New Items to Existing Client Orders</strong></p><p>Implemented a feature that checks if a client already has an active order.</p><p> If an order exists, new requested items are added to their current order instead of creating a new one.</p><p> Ensured the system merges items correctly and updates totals accurately.</p><p>? <strong>3. Backend &amp; UI Improvements</strong></p><p>Optimized order-handling logic for better performance.</p><p> Updated UI messages and flow to make actions clearer to staff.</p><p> Improved accuracy of order summaries and stock reflections on the dashboard.</p><p>? <strong>4. Responsiveness &amp; Testing</strong></p><p>Tested all updates across devices to ensure smooth usage.</p><p> Verified that order updates, stock changes, and UI responses are consistent across mobile, tablet, and desktop.</p><p>? <strong>Summary</strong></p><p>The Aby Dash system now offers:</p><p>? Accurate stock updates</p><p> ? Automatic merging of new items into existing client orders</p><p> ? Improved backend logic and UI clarity</p><p> ? Full responsiveness and stable performance</p><p>These updates make the stock and ordering process more efficient, reduce errors, and improve overall system reliability.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-29 20:51:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('04ebb94a-da10-4818-8175-7ebcbe199699','? Gacuruzi Barber Shop App – In-App Update Feature (Work in Progress) Report','\"\\\"<h1>? <strong>Gacuruzi Barber Shop App – In-App Update Feature (Work in Progress) Report</strong></h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Ishimwe Serge</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on adding a <strong>new update feature</strong> to the <strong>Gacuruzi Barber Shop Mobile App</strong>. The goal of this feature is to allow the app to <strong>detect and receive new updates</strong> without requiring users to manually check for them. The feature is currently in progress and not yet fully completed.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. Update Feature Setup (In Progress)</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Started implementing logic that checks for new app updates.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Prepared the app to receive update information when a new version is available.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Laid the foundation for notifying users about updates inside the app.</li></ol><h4>⚙️ 2. Backend / Update Flow Preparation</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Structured how update data will be fetched and processed by the app.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Began integrating update checks into the app lifecycle.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured the implementation does not affect existing app functionality.</li></ol><h4>? 3. Initial Testing &amp; Adjustments</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested the update flow in development mode.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Fixed early issues discovered during testing.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Identified remaining tasks needed to complete the feature properly.</li></ol><h3>? Current Status</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>The update feature is <strong>partially implemented</strong>.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Core logic is in place, but final validation, UI prompts, and full testing are still required.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work introduced the foundation for an <strong>in-app update system</strong> in the Gacuruzi Barber Shop App:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Base logic for checking updates</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>⚙️ Safe integration without breaking existing features</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Feature currently under development</li></ol><p>Once completed, this feature will allow users to easily stay on the latest version of the app.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-01 20:31:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('069b7e7b-d493-40b8-acac-a555afdc11ab','? Menu Category Backend Development','\"\\\"<h2>? Menu Category Backend Development</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Honore</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>backend side of the menu category feature</strong>. The focus was on ensuring that menu categories can be <strong>fetched, updated, and deleted</strong> reliably to support frontend operations and overall system functionality.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>?️ <strong>Fetching Menu Categories</strong></h4><p>Implemented backend endpoints to fetch all menu categories.</p><p> Ensured data is returned in a clean and structured format for frontend use.</p><p> Optimized queries to improve performance and reliability.</p><h4>✏️ <strong>Updating Menu Categories</strong></h4><p>Developed backend logic to update existing menu category details.</p><p> Added validation to prevent invalid or empty updates.</p><p> Ensured updates are reflected immediately across the system.</p><h4>?️ <strong>Deleting Menu Categories</strong></h4><p>Implemented secure deletion of menu categories.</p><p> Handled edge cases to prevent deleting categories that are in active use.</p><p> Improved error handling to avoid unexpected backend failures.</p><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work strengthened the backend of menu category management:</p><p>?️ <strong>Reliable APIs:</strong> Stable endpoints for fetching, updating, and deleting categories.</p><p> ? <strong>Data Integrity:</strong> Validations and checks ensure safe operations.</p><p> ⚙️ <strong>System Support:</strong> Backend fully supports frontend category management features.</p><p>These backend improvements ensure smooth and reliable menu category management across the system.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-12 19:29:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('0751ee1e-a59d-41ec-a294-68e46dd835ba','?️ General System Improvements – Daily Work Progress Report','\"\\\"<h1>?️ <strong>General System Improvements – Daily Work Progress Report</strong></h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Honore</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I focused on improving different parts of the system to enhance performance, stability, and overall user experience. The goal was to refine existing features and make sure the platform runs smoothly for all users.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. System Cleanup &amp; Optimization</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Reviewed several sections of the platform to identify slow or inefficient areas.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved performance by cleaning unused code, reducing unnecessary re-renders, and optimizing UI components.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured faster loading speeds and smoother navigation across the system.</li></ol><h4>? 2. Bug Fixes &amp; Minor Adjustments</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Fixed various small bugs reported by the team and users.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved reliability of specific components that were occasionally failing.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured that all updated areas now behave consistently.</li></ol><h4>? 3. User Experience Improvements</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Adjusted UI elements to make interactions more intuitive.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved spacing, readability, and layout consistency in some sections.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured the updated interfaces work well on mobile and desktop.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work focused on making the system more stable, responsive, and user-friendly through:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Technical optimization</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Bug fixing</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? UI/UX improvements</li></ol><p>These updates contribute to overall system quality and prepare the platform for upcoming features.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-27 19:22:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('08f29ab1-9d50-4558-af93-d3bc875376df','Steps for Efficient Reporting System and Forum Management','\"\\\"<p>Managing a reporting system alongside a forum website is essential for maintaining an organized, safe, and engaging online environment. A structured approach ensures that user reports are handled efficiently, forum content is moderated appropriately, and users can navigate and participate effectively. This report outlines key strategies for managing reports and forum operations, focusing on organization, user engagement, system integration, and security</p><p><br></p><p><strong>1. Organize Reports</strong></p><p> All incoming reports should be received, categorized, and prioritized to ensure timely resolution. Tracking progress of each report helps maintain accountability and ensures no issues are overlooked.</p><p><strong>2. Moderate Content</strong></p><p> Forum discussions should be regularly monitored to remove spam or inappropriate content. Maintaining clear community guidelines promotes a safe and respectful environment for all users.</p><p><strong>3. Enhance Navigation</strong></p><p> Organizing forum topics into categories and subforums improves usability. Adding search functionality allows users to quickly find relevant discussions, making the platform more user-friendly.</p><p><strong>4. Engage Users</strong></p><p> Notifications, discussion prompts, and user profiles encourage active participation. Engaging users increases interaction, builds community, and supports feedback collection.</p><p><strong>5. Integrate Systems</strong></p><p> Linking reporting system alerts to moderators allows faster responses to flagged forum content. Integration streamlines workflow and improves issue resolution efficiency.</p><p><strong>6. Analyze Data</strong></p><p> Monitoring trends and recurring issues provides insights to improve both the reporting system and forum management processes. Data-driven decisions enhance overall performance.</p><p><strong>7. Maintain Security</strong></p><p> Implementing access controls, performing regular backups, and monitoring system performance prevents data loss and ensures reliable operations.</p><h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3><p>Efficient management of reporting systems and forum websites requires a combination of organization, moderation, user engagement, integration, data analysis, and security. By following these strategies, administrators can create a safe, responsive, and interactive online community, ensuring issues are resolved promptly and users remain engaged.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-23 16:06:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('0bd0810a-049e-4e31-871d-efa63f2af726','? Aby Inventory Management – Deployment of New Changes','\"\\\"<h2>? Aby Inventory Management – Deployment of New Changes</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Prince</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Aby Inventory System</strong>, focusing on <strong>deploying the latest updates</strong>. The goal was to make all the new features and improvements available to users, ensuring the system runs smoothly with the latest changes.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? <strong>Deployment of Updates</strong></h4><p>Deployed the latest frontend and backend changes to the production environment.</p><p> Ensured that <strong>debt recording features, dashboard updates, and offline improvements</strong> were included in the deployment.</p><p> Tested the system post-deployment to confirm that all functionalities work as expected.</p><h4>?️ <strong>Post-Deployment Checks</strong></h4><p>Verified that stock-out entries, debt tracking, and dashboard statistics are working correctly.</p><p> Ensured offline syncing mechanisms are operational for users without internet access.</p><p> Fixed minor issues found during deployment testing to maintain system stability.</p><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work ensured the Aby Inventory System is <strong>up-to-date and fully functional</strong>:</p><p>? <strong>Deployed New Features:</strong> All recent updates are live for users.</p><p> ?️ <strong>System Validation:</strong> Checked critical functionalities for accuracy and reliability.</p><p> ⚙️ <strong>Stable Environment:</strong> Minor post-deployment fixes applied to maintain smooth operation.</p><p>This deployment ensures that users have access to the latest enhancements and improvements in Aby Inventory.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-10 15:02:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('0bed3037-6266-43f1-8ca0-420d906edf62','⚡ Aby Inventory – Real-Time Stock Requisition Updates','\"\\\"<h1>⚡ <strong>Aby Inventory – Real-Time Stock Requisition Updates</strong></h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Prince</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Aby Inventory system</strong>, focusing on enabling <strong>real-time updates</strong> for stock requisitions. The aim was to ensure that all users see changes instantly without needing to refresh the page.</p><h3>✅ Work Completed</h3><h4>? Real-Time Stock Requisition Handling</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented <strong>real-time synchronization</strong> for stock requisition data.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured updates such as creation, approval, rejection, and receiving appear instantly.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Linked real-time updates to the requisition dashboard for live status changes.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved system responsiveness to enhance user experience.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested real-time behavior to confirm accuracy across different user roles.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>The real-time requisition feature now allows:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Immediate visibility of stock requisition changes</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Better coordination between admins and employees</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Faster decision-making and smoother workflows</li></ol><p>This update significantly improves efficiency and reliability in the inventory system.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-08 20:55:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('0dc797fa-085d-4cb1-90e6-ed84d34ab38f','? Aby Dash – Performance Tracking Report (Frontend)','\"\\\"<p><br></p><h2>? Aby Dash – Performance Tracking Report (Frontend)</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Shema Serge</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>I worked on implementing the <strong>PDF export feature</strong> for the Performance Tracking reports on the frontend. The goal was to allow users to export performance data into a downloadable PDF for reporting and review purposes.</p><h3>?️ Work Done</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented the frontend logic for exporting <strong>Performance Tracking reports</strong> to PDF</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Connected performance data (kitchen efficiency, revenue tracking, peak hours, etc.) to the export feature</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Designed the PDF layout structure to match the report view on the frontend</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested the PDF export functionality across different report sections</li></ol><h3>⚠️ Current Status / Challenges</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>The PDF export feature is <strong>not working very well yet</strong></li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Some data is not rendering correctly in the generated PDF</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Layout and formatting issues occur during export</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Further optimization and fixes are required to ensure accuracy and stability</li></ol><h3>? Next Steps</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Debug data rendering issues</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improve PDF layout and styling</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Optimize export performance for large datasets</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Retest across different browsers and report scenarios</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>The PDF export functionality for the Performance Tracking frontend report has been implemented, but it still requires improvements and fixes to work reliably and meet the expected reporting quality.</p><p><br></p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-02-04 20:22:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('111b9dd3-968a-471e-943b-9cec96582ad5','? Chat Functionality Development Report','\"\\\"<h2>? Chat Functionality Development Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Ishimwe Serge</p><h3>? Report Overview</h3><p>I worked on implementing a <strong>chat functionality</strong> within the system to improve communication between users. The goal was to allow users to exchange messages easily and also share files directly through the chat interface.</p><h3>?️ Work Done</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented real-time chat functionality that allows users to send and receive messages smoothly</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Added support for <strong>file sharing</strong>, enabling users to send documents and other files through the chat</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured messages and files are delivered correctly without affecting system performance</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Focused on making the chat interface simple, clear, and easy to use</li></ol><h3>? Impact</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved communication between users inside the system</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Made collaboration easier by allowing file sharing within conversations</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Reduced the need for external communication tools</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This feature adds an important communication layer to the system by enabling chatting and file sharing. It helps users interact more efficiently and makes the system more practical for day-to-day collaboration.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-02-05 18:45:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('11df2c44-face-49d4-9adc-4e9d7fddd024','? Backend Debt Fetching Report','\"\\\"<h2><strong>? Backend Debt Fetching Report</strong></h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Honore Mihigo</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>I worked on the backend side of the system to properly support debt management by ensuring that debt data can be fetched correctly and reliably. The main goal was to make debt information available for use by the frontend and other system features without errors or inconsistencies.</p><h3>✅ Work Done</h3><h4><strong>? Backend Logic for Fetching Debt</strong></h4><p>I implemented and refined backend logic responsible for fetching debt records from the database. This involved structuring queries and responses so that all relevant debt details are retrieved accurately and in a usable format.</p><h4><strong>⚙️ API Support for Debt Data</strong></h4><p>I ensured that backend endpoints return complete and consistent debt data that can be consumed by the frontend. This allows the system to display correct debt information wherever it is required, such as dashboards, reports, or stock-out processes.</p><h4><strong>?️ Data Reliability &amp; Stability</strong></h4><p>I focused on making the debt fetching process stable by handling possible issues such as missing data or incorrect responses. This helps prevent errors and ensures the system behaves reliably when accessing debt-related information.</p><h3>? Impact</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Debt information can now be fetched smoothly from the backend</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Frontend features depending on debt data can function correctly</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved consistency and reliability of debt-related system operations</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This work strengthened the backend foundation for debt management by ensuring debt data can be fetched accurately and consistently, making it easier for other parts of the system to use and display this information effectively.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-21 16:33:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('1249e71d-a826-4f1a-aa0e-1521580de8c7','? Aby Inventory – Stock Requisition Approval (Backend)','\"\\\"<h1>? <strong>Aby Inventory – Stock Requisition Approval (Backend)</strong></h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Honore</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Aby Inventory system</strong>, focusing on the backend logic for <strong>stock requisition approval</strong>. The aim was to ensure that requisitions are properly reviewed and controlled before affecting stock.</p><h3>✅ Work Completed</h3><h4>✔️ Stock Requisition Approval Backend</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented backend functionality to <strong>approve stock requisitions</strong>.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured only authorized users (admin) can approve requisitions.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Added logic to update requisition status a