sers.</p><p><br></p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-02 20:43:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('4d596b17-7ecb-43e8-891d-71ad31f8048e','? Aby Dash – Expenses Management Bug Fix','\"\\\"<h2>? Aby Dash – Expenses Management Bug Fix</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Prince Mihigo</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on <strong>Aby Dash</strong>, focusing on fixing issues in the <strong>expenses management module</strong>. The main problem was that the system could not properly fetch all expenses and did not allow users to edit existing expense records.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>?️ <strong>Expenses Fetching Fix</strong></h4><p>Identified and fixed the issue preventing expenses from being fetched correctly.</p><p> Ensured that all expense records are now loaded and displayed as expected.</p><p> Improved error handling to avoid failed or incomplete data loading.</p><h4>✏️ <strong>Expense Editing Fix</strong></h4><p>Resolved the issue that was blocking users from editing expense details.</p><p> Ensured that expense updates are saved correctly and reflected immediately.</p><p> Tested editing functionality to confirm smooth and reliable operation.</p><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work restored proper functionality to the expenses management feature in Aby Dash:</p><p>? <strong>Expenses Display:</strong> All expenses now fetch and display correctly.</p><p> ✏️ <strong>Editing Enabled:</strong> Users can edit expenses without errors.</p><p> ⚙️ <strong>System Stability:</strong> Improved reliability of the expenses management module.</p><p>These fixes ensure a smoother and more reliable experience when managing expenses in Aby Dash.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-12 20:17:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('4ed1e292-272b-4720-915a-14023c65cb5c','backend updates for the notification management system','\"\\\"<p><strong>Today I worked on</strong> backend updates for the notification management system.</p><p><br></p><p>The purpose of today’s work was to strengthen the backend foundations of the notification engine supporting leave management, risk alerts, and presales updates. The objective was to improve consistency, reliability, and responsiveness across all modules that depend on server-triggered notifications.</p><h3><strong>Body of the Report</strong></h3><p>The main focus was on enhancing the event-triggering logic and expanding the API endpoints used by the frontend. This included refining the rules that determine when a notification should be generated and adjusting message formats so the frontend receives clear, structured data. Additional effort was dedicated to improving the scheduling process for time-based alerts to ensure that notifications are dispatched without delay.</p><h3><strong>Challenges Encountered</strong></h3><p>A key obstacle was inconsistent firing of certain notification events, particularly those related to risk updates. The trigger conditions were too broad, which sometimes caused premature or duplicate alerts. There was also an issue with the internal queue not processing certain batches of notifications correctly.</p><h3><strong>How the Challenges Were Fixed</strong></h3><p>The trigger logic was redefined with stricter conditional boundaries, ensuring events are recognized only when specific criteria are met. The queue processor was debugged and optimized by adding logs and adjusting timeout configurations, which resolved the issue with incomplete batches.</p><h3><strong>Why This Approach Was Chosen</strong></h3><p>A logic-first refinement was selected because it provides a scalable solution that avoids the need for repeated manual fixes. Tightening the conditions ensures higher accuracy, and improving the processor stability prevents future bottlenecks as the system grows.</p><h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3><p>The backend is now more reliable and prepared to handle real-time communication with the frontend. These improvements contribute directly to better user experience and a more predictable notification system.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-17 21:15:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('4f0eed2e-d5c0-4b38-9290-bf869fd70cd3','? System Demonstration & Device Setup Report – Golden Park (Nyamata)','\"\\\"<h2>? System Demonstration &amp; Device Setup Report – Golden Park (Nyamata)</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Prince</p><h3>? Report Overview</h3><p>I went to <strong>Golden Park Company in Nyamata</strong> to demonstrate how the system works and to guide the team through its main features. The visit focused on helping them understand the system workflow and preparing them to start using it confidently in their daily operations.</p><h3>?️ Activities Carried Out</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Explained how the system functions, from basic navigation to key operational features</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Demonstrated real use cases to show how the system supports daily business activities</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Guided the staff on how to correctly use the system in their work environment</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Identified and collected the <strong>devices</strong> (such as tablets and related equipment) that the company will be using with the system</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Verified that the selected devices are suitable and compatible with the system requirements</li></ol><h3>? Impact</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>The company gained a clear understanding of how the system operates</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Staff are now better prepared to use the system effectively</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Devices to be used were clearly identified, helping with proper setup and planning</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This visit helped ensure that <strong>Golden Park in Nyamata</strong> understands how the system works and is ready to use it. By demonstrating the system and confirming the devices they will be using, the foundation was set for smooth adoption and effective daily use.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-02-05 19:36:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('500d5b5c-af70-42e0-b547-647ffe2a22af','? Menu Category Company Association Report','\"\\\"<h2>? Menu Category Company Association Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Serge Shema</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>I worked on enhancing the system so that menu categories are properly managed on a per-company basis. The goal was to make sure the system supports multiple companies without data conflicts, especially when it comes to organizing menu items.</p><h3>✅ Detailed Work Done</h3><h4>? Company-Based Menu Category Management</h4><p>I implemented changes that ensure <strong>each company has its own set of menu categories</strong>. Menu categories are now strictly linked to the company that created them, which prevents categories from appearing or being used by other companies on the system.</p><h4>? Proper Association Logic</h4><p>The system now enforces a clear relationship between companies and their menu categories. When a company creates, edits, or deletes a menu category, those actions only affect that specific company’s data. This improves data isolation and system reliability.</p><h4>? Data Separation &amp; Control</h4><p>Added checks to avoid cross-company access, ensuring one company cannot view or assign menu categories belonging to another company. This helps maintain clean data boundaries and avoids confusion during menu management.</p><h3>? Impact</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved multi-company support</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Better organization of menu data</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Reduced risk of data conflicts</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>More scalable system design for future growth</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This work strengthened the system’s foundation by ensuring menu categories are fully company-specific. It allows businesses to manage their menus independently while keeping the overall platform secure, organized, and ready to scale.</p><p><br></p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-20 17:06:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('50964b6c-dec2-4e04-80f1-4a59c6f95800','? Backend Development Report','\"\\\"<h2>? Backend Development Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Honore</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>I worked on the <strong>backend side of the system</strong>, supporting ongoing development by improving backend logic and ensuring features function correctly. The focus was on strengthening backend processes that support reports and core system functionality.</p><h3>✅ Work Done</h3><h4>⚙️ Backend Development Tasks</h4><p>Worked on backend logic to support system features and reporting needs.</p><p> Improved data handling to ensure accurate fetching and processing of information.</p><p> Refined backend code to align with current system requirements.</p><h4>? Testing &amp; Validation</h4><p>Tested backend functionality to confirm correct behavior.