Features','\"\\\"<h2>? Aby Inventory Dashboard &amp; Debt Features</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Shema Serge</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Aby Inventory System</strong>, focusing on enhancing the <strong>dashboard and sales report pages</strong>. The goal was to improve <strong>debt visibility and statistics</strong>, allowing users to filter summaries by date and see debt information clearly on sales reports.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? <strong>Dashboard Updates</strong></h4><p>Added a <strong>filter by date</strong> to the dashboard summary to allow users to view data for specific periods.</p><p> Created a <strong>debt statistics card</strong> to show total outstanding debts at a glance.</p><p> Ensured that dashboard data updates dynamically based on selected dates.</p><h4>? <strong>Sales Report Updates</strong></h4><p>Updated the sales report page to <strong>display debt information</strong> for each sale.</p><p> Improved UI for clearer debt tracking alongside sales data.</p><p> Ensured consistency between debt records on the dashboard and sales reports.</p><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work improved Aby Inventory’s frontend for better debt management:</p><p>? <strong>Dashboard Filtering:</strong> Users can now filter summaries by date.</p><p> ? <strong>Debt Stats Card:</strong> Quick overview of outstanding debts.</p><p> ? <strong>Sales Report Debt Display:</strong> Debt information is visible directly in sales reports.</p><p>These updates make it easier for users to track debts across the system and analyze sales and financial performance more efficiently.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-09 14:54:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('7d3f353a-92be-465d-8869-757f43ca5be7','✅ Aby Inventory – Stock Requisition Approval & Item Adjustment (Backend)','\"\\\"<p><br></p><h1>✅ <strong>Aby Inventory – Stock Requisition Approval &amp; Item Adjustment (Backend)</strong></h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Honore</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Aby Inventory system</strong>, focusing on the <strong>stock requisition approval process</strong>. The main goal was to give admins full control during approval, including the ability to manage items within a requisition.</p><h3>✅ Work Completed</h3><h4>?️ Stock Requisition Approval Enhancements</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented the <strong>approval workflow</strong> for stock requisitions.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured only <strong>admins</strong> can approve requisitions.</li></ol><h4>➕➖ Item Management During Approval</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Added functionality allowing admins to <strong>add new items</strong> while approving a requisition.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Enabled admins to <strong>edit item details</strong> such as quantity and pricing.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Allowed admins to <strong>remove items</strong> from a requisition if necessary.</li></ol><h4>? Pricing Control</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Required admins to set both <strong>purchasing price</strong> and <strong>selling price</strong> for any newly added items.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Validated pricing fields to prevent approval without proper price configuration.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured pricing changes are correctly saved and reflected in inventory records.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>These improvements give admins flexible and full control over stock requisitions by allowing them to:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Approve requests with confidence</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Adjust, add, or remove items as needed</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensure all items have correct purchasing and selling prices</li></ol><p>This strengthens accuracy, accountability, and data consistency in the inventory system.</p><p><br></p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-06 20:46:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('7d444a8c-f86d-48e0-8e62-bbff92407052','? Daily Work Progress Report','\"\\\"<h1>? Daily Work Progress Report</h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Honore Mihigo</p><p> <strong>Position:</strong> Backend Developer</p><p> <strong>Date:</strong> 13 October 2025</p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>AbyTech Platform</strong>, focusing on building the foundations for the new <strong>Notification Management</strong> system. The goal was to start setting up how notifications will be handled, stored, and delivered across the platform. The feature is not fully completed yet, but major progress has been made.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. Notification Management Setup</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Started developing the <strong>Notification Management module</strong> to support system-wide alerts and updates.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Designed the initial structure for handling notifications in the backend, including:</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>How notifications are stored</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>How they are linked to users</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Basic triggers for generating notifications</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Created early backend logic to allow notifications to be created and saved in the system.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested sample notifications to make sure the system accepts and records them correctly.</li></ol><h4>⚙️ 2. Preparing for Full Integration</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Set up the base API routes that will later be used by the frontend to retrieve notifications.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured the system is ready for more advanced features such as:</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Marking notifications as read</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Real-time updates</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Filtering by type (expense, report, assignment, etc.)</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Identified ar