n class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured the Blogs Page is fully responsive across all devices.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved alignment, spacing, and scaling so the page looks clean on phones, tablets, and desktops.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work on the E4H Initiative website included:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Developing a modern and clean Blogs Page</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Improving blog readability and user navigation</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Making the page responsive on all devices</li></ol><p>These updates help the E4H platform present its stories and updates more professionally and make the site more engaging for visitors.</p><p>\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"</p><p>\\\\\\\"</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-24 20:01:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('82808916-e07d-4381-8f14-0202f6739440','Pipeline Integration Report',NULL,'https://res.cloudinary.com/dfavs66eh/raw/upload/v1762902616/abytech/report/ghmnzvqrxrvq0eiqhaby.pdf','abytech/report/ghmnzvqrxrvq0eiqhaby.pdf','2025-11-11 19:22:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('82ccb7af-42f8-4dc0-bb63-a745f807e28c','Aby Dash – Drink Category & Order Integration Report','\"\\\"<h1><strong>Aby Dash – Drink Category &amp; Order Integration Report</strong></h1><p>Name: Ishimwe Serge</p><p> Position: Frontend Developer</p><p><br></p><p>? <strong>Introduction</strong></p><p>Today, I completed updates on the Aby Dash system by adding new drink category names and integrating them into the order workflow. The goal was to make the drink ordering process clearer, more organized, and fully aligned with the menu item categories.</p><p>✅ <strong>Key Tasks Completed</strong></p><p>? <strong>1. Added Final Drink Names to the System/Menu</strong></p><p>Integrated the finalized list of drink names into the menu structure:</p><p>✔️ <strong>Liquor (Shots Category)</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Single Shot</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Double Shot</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Quarter Shot</li></ol><p>✔️ <strong>Wine (Glass Category)</strong></p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Wine Glass</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Wine Bottle</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Wine Carton</li></ol><p>These names are now clean, standardized, and ready for use across the system.</p><p>? <strong>2. Integrated Drink Items Into the Ordering Flow</strong></p><p>Configured the order section so drinks can now be added directly from the menu items.</p><p> Ensured each drink correctly maps to its category based on type.</p><p>?️ <strong>3. Category Logic for Drink Serving</strong></p><p>Implemented logic so the system automatically uses the correct <em>serve category</em>:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>If the selected drink is <strong>Liquor</strong>, the system uses the <strong>Liquor Serving Category</strong> (Single, Double, Quarter Shot).</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>If the drink is <strong>Wine</strong>, it uses the <strong>Wine Serving Category</strong> (Glass, Bottle, Carton).</li></ol><p>This makes ordering more accurate and prevents mixing categories.</p><p>? <strong>4. UI/UX Improvements for Selection</strong></p><p>Improved the drink selection interface for clarity.</p><p> Made category options easy to understand and visually clean.</p><p> Ensured users can quickly choose the serving size without confusion.</p><p>? <strong>Summary</strong></p><p>The Aby Dash system now includes:</p><p>? Finalized drink names added to the menu</p><p> ? Smooth integration into the ordering workflow</p><p> ?️ Correct category serving logic for Liquor and Wine</p><p> ? A clearer and more user-friendly drink selection UI</p><p>These updates ensure the ordering process is accurate, organized, and ready for real business use.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-12-02 20:54:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('82f211b1-de8d-43b3-b23d-0b124cef7239','? Daily Work Progress Report','\"\\\"<h1>? Daily Work Progress Report</h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Prince</p><p> <strong>Position:</strong> Backend &amp; System Developer</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on transforming the <strong>Aby Booking Web Platform</strong> into a <strong>Progressive Web App (PWA)</strong>. The goal was to make Aby Booking installable like a mobile app, improve offline support, and deliver a faster, more app-like experience for users.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. Progressive Web App Conversion</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Successfully converted <strong>Aby Booking</strong> into a fully functional <strong>PWA</strong>.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Added the required <strong>manifest file</strong> containing app name, icons, theme colors, and display settings.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Configured <strong>service workers</strong> to handle caching, offline access, and background tasks.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured the app can be <strong>installed on mobile and desktop devices</strong> directly from the browser.</li></ol><h4>⚙️ 2. Offline Capability &amp; Performance</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Set up caching strategies to allow key pages and assets to load even without internet connection.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved loading performance to make the app feel faster and more responsive.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Verified that the PWA works smoothly after installation, just like a native app.</li></ol><h4>? 3. Testing Across Devices</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested the install and launch process on Android, iOS (Safari support where possible), and desktop browsers.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured the app icon, splash screen, and layout behave correctly across devices.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Confirmed smooth transitions between online and offline modes.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work successfully transformed <strong>Aby Booking</strong> into a <strong>Progressive Web App</strong>, bringing major improvements:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? <strong>Installable App Experience:</strong> Users can now install Aby Booking on their devices.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>⚙️ <strong>Offline Support:</strong> Core features and UI load even without internet.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>⚡ <strong>Better Performance:</strong> Faster loading and smoother navigation.</li></ol><p>These updates make Aby Booking feel more modern, accessible, and user-friendly — offering a true app-like experience on both mobile and desktop.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-14 19:11:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('8636edd4-67d5-4202-ad08-62ec967a7f94','? Daily Work Progress Report','\"\\\"<h1>? Daily Work Progress Report</h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Shema Serge</p><p> <strong>Position:</strong> Software Developer</p><p><br></p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Employee Order Form</strong> feature. The goal was to allow employees to create and submit orders easily from their side of the system. This helps improve internal ordering and makes the process more organized for both employees and management.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. Employee Order Form Setup</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Created the basic <strong>Employee Order Form</strong> where employees can fill in details for items they want to request.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Added input fields such as:</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Item name</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Quantity</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Description or reason for the request</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Made sure the form is simple and easy for employees to use.</li></ol><h4>? 2. Connecting the Form to the System</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Set up backend connections so every form submission is <strong>saved correctly in the database</strong>.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured that each order is linked to the correct employee profile.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested the ordering flow to confirm that all information is passed and stored properly.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s progress completed the first version of the <strong>Employee Order Form</strong>:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Employees can now fill and submit item requests.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? Orders are saved correctly and linked to the employee.</li></ol><p>This feature makes ordering smoother and helps companies manage employee requests more efficiently.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'202