class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Clearly track received items</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Maintain accurate requisition status</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improve stock flow visibility</li></ol><p>This update helps complete the requisition lifecycle smoothly within the inventory system.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-05 20:22:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('8b124d20-49c5-44d1-9383-f7f02cbc9186','? Barber Shop App – Firebase Backend Setup Report','\"\\\"<h1>? <strong>Barber Shop App – Firebase Backend Setup Report</strong></h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Prince</p><p> <strong>Position:</strong> Backend Developer</p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on setting up the <strong>backend infrastructure</strong> for the <strong>Barber Shop Application</strong> using <strong>Firebase</strong>. The goal was to create a reliable, scalable backend that supports authentication, data storage, and appointment management.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. Firebase Project Setup</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Created and configured the Firebase project for the barber shop system.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Set up Firebase Authentication for secure user login and session handling.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Configured Firestore as the main database for storing application data.</li></ol><h4>? 2. Database Structure Design</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Designed Firestore collections for users, appointments, and availability.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Structured documents to support appointment booking with a single barber.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured data relationships are clean and easy to query.</li></ol><h4>? 3. Security Rules Configuration</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented Firebase security rules to protect user and appointment data.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured only authenticated users can create or view their appointments.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Restricted admin-only actions where necessary.</li></ol><h4>? 4. Backend Support for Frontend Integration</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Prepared APIs and data access logic for frontend usage.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested data creation, reading, and updates from the client app.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured real-time updates work correctly for appointment availability.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s backend work established a solid Firebase foundation by delivering:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? A fully configured Firebase project</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" conten