editable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved the <strong>mobile app’s structure and performance</strong>, optimizing components for smoother navigation and faster response times.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Refined API integration between the mobile frontend and the backend to ensure real-time synchronization of booking data.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Enhanced error handling and network response feedback to improve user reliability, even under weak internet connections.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Updated the app’s navigation flow for a more intuitive user journey — from browsing menu items to completing an order.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Worked on fixing minor UI inconsistencies to make the design more uniform and user-friendly.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Conducted testing on multiple devices to verify layout consistency and proper functionality across Android and iOS.</li></ol><p>✅ <strong>Result:</strong> The Aby Booking Mobile App now runs faster, looks cleaner, and provides a smoother experience from login to booking confirmation.</p><h4>⚙️ 2. Backend Optimization</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved backend endpoints to deliver data more efficiently to the mobile app.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Reduced unnecessary requests and optimized response structures to minimize loading times.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured that updates in menu items, partners, and orders reflect instantly on the mobile side.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Strengthened error handling to reduce failed booking attempts caused by server delays.</li></ol><p>✅ <strong>Result:</strong> Backend and mobile app integration now operates seamlessly, allowing users to browse, order, and confirm bookings effortlessly.</p><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today’s work on <strong>Aby Booking Mobile</strong> focused on improving performance, integration, and overall usability:</p><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>? <strong>Mobile App Optimization:</strong> Faster loading, smoother navigation, and improved UI consistency.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>⚙️ <strong>Backend Integration:</strong> Enhanced API efficiency and real-time synchronization between app and server.</li></ol><p>These improvements make the <strong>Aby Booking Mobile Application</strong> more stable, responsive, and ready for a better user experience across all devices.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-11 22:02:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('982a9428-d6c4-428c-adbe-83e5d8fe264c','Debt Logic Update Report','\"\\\"<h2>? Work Progress Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Ishimwe Serge</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>Tomorrow, I worked on improving the <strong>debt handling logic</strong> in the system by allowing users to <strong>set debt even when the payment amount is zero</strong>. This change was important to support real business scenarios where a transaction can be fully recorded as debt without any upfront payment.</p><h3>✅ Work Done</h3><h4>? Debt Logic Enhancement</h4><p>Updated the system to allow recording a transaction with <strong>0 payment</strong>, while still correctly registering it as debt.</p><p>Reviewed how debt and payment data are handled to ensure the system correctly understands zero payment as intentional, not an error.</p><h4>? Backend Logic Refactor</h4><p>This change required <strong>reworking the existing logic</strong>, since the previous flow assumed that some payment must always be made.</p><p>Adjusted conditions and calculations so debt, payment, and balances remain accurate even when payment is zero.</p><h4>? Testing &amp; Validation</h4><p>Tested different scenarios including partial payment, full payment, and zero payment.</p><p>Verified that reports, summaries, and related features still behave correctly after the logic change.</p><h3>? Impact</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>System now supports real-world debt scenarios more accurately</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Zero-payment transactions are handled correctly without breaking logic</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved flexibility and reliability of the debt management feature</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This work involved changing the core debt logic to allow zero-payment transactions. It required rethinking and updating the existing flow, resulting in a more flexible and realistic debt handling system that better supports daily operations.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-27 23:02:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('985400f6-cbc8-4b27-b4dd-6603cefc0db2','? Deployment Report','\"\\\"<p><br></p><h2>? Deployment Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Prince Mihigo</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>I worked on deploying the <strong>latest changes</strong> to the system, ensuring that all new features, fixes, and improvements were properly moved to the live environment and made available for users.</p><h3>✅ Work Done</h3><h4>? Deployment of New Changes</h4><p>Deployed the newly developed updates to the production environment.</p><p>Ensured all services were running correctly after deployment.</p><p>Verified that recent features and fixes were working as expected in the live system.</p><h4>? Post-Deployment Checks</h4><p>Monitored the system after deployment to confirm stability and performance.</p><p>Resolved minor issues that could affect system functionality.</p><p>Confirmed that the deployed changes matched the intended updates.</p><h3>? Impact</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>New features and improvements are now live and accessible</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>System remains stable after deployment</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\&quot;bullet\\\\\\\\&quot;\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Users can benefit from the latest updates without disruption</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This work ensured a smooth and successful deployment of new system changes, making sure everything was properly released to production and functioning as expected.</p><p><br></p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-22 18:33:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('98c1a7cd-2a11-42b3-8aa9-742d7e156046','Expense Management App – Feature Organization & UX Improvements','\"\\\"<p>Work centered on improving the Expense Management App by organizing core features and enhancing usability for daily financial tracking.</p><h3>Key Improvements</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Structured folders around core modules such as <strong>expenses</strong>, <strong>categories</strong>, <strong>reports</strong>, and <strong>user settings</strong>.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved UI clarity for adding, editing, and categorizing expenses.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Enhanced expense listing screens with better spacing, clearer labels, and improved data grouping.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Optimized forms to reduce input errors and speed up expense entry.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Laid groundwork for future features such as monthly summaries, exports, and multi-account support.</li></ol><h3>Result</h3><p>The app is now more intuitive and efficient, helping users manage expenses faster while providing a solid technical foundation for future enhancements.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-12-23 06:03:00.000','6a8aa455-94f0-4e98-92e7-809c64adcfe4'),('9920c76b-65e5-481e-8bf8-21da16fceb39','Efficient Management of Reporting Systems and Forum Websites','\"\\\"<p>\\\\\\\"</p><p>Managing a reporting system alongside a forum website requires a careful balance between technical organization and user experience. Efficient systems ensure that user issues are resolved promptly while providing a safe, interactive space for community engagement. This report outlines key strategies for handling reports, moderating forums, enhancing user interaction, and maintaining system security.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>1. Reporting System Management</strong></p><p>A reporting system allows members to submit issues, suggestions, or complaints. These submissions should be categorized and prioritized to enable quick resolution. Regular tracking of report status ensures accountability and helps identify recurring patterns, providing insights to improve overall system processes.</p><p><strong>2. Forum Management</strong></p><p>Forum management focuses on creating an engaging and organized community space. This includes moderating discussions to enforce guidelines, structuring topics for easy navigation, and incorporating features like search tools, notifications, and user profiles to enhance user interaction.</p><p><strong>3. Security and Maintenance</strong></p><p>Security measures such as access controls, regular backups, and system monitoring prevent disruptions and safeguard user trust. Maintaining system reliability ensures continuous engagement and protects data integrity.</p><p><strong>4. System Integration and Feedback</strong></p><p>Integrating the reporting system with forum operations streamlines responses. Flagged posts can automatically alert moderators, reducing response times and improving satisfaction. Encouraging user feedback and performing periodic system updates further enhance efficiency and user experience.</p><h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3><p> in managing both the reporting system and forum website is vital for operational efficiency and a positive online community. By combining structured reporting with dynamic forum management, it is possible to foster a responsive, secure, and engaging platform that meets both administrative and user needs.</p><p>\\\\\\\"</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-23 12:04:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('9c27fb66-b768-4047-9697-c7ade7e7e929','implementing and refining the frontend browser-notification features','\"\\\"<h3><strong>Introduction</strong></h3><p>The goal of today’s tasks was to complete the interface that receives and displays notifications coming from the backend. This includes making sure browser permissions behave correctly and the user sees relevant alerts immediately.</p><h3><strong>Body of the Report</strong></h3><p>Most of the day was spent integrating the updated backend endpoints and testing how notifications appear across various browsers. The visual layout of the notification panel was also improved so users can easily identify the type of alert—whether it relates to leave updates, risk issues, or presales activities.</p><h3><strong>Challenges Encountered</strong></h3><p>One significant challenge was handling differences in how browsers request permission for notifications. Some browsers suppressed alerts silently, while others required explicit user confirmation. Additionally, there were formatting mismatches between backend data and frontend rendering.</p><h3><strong>How the Challenges Were Fixed</strong></h3><p>A standardized permission handler was implemented, ensuring all browsers follow the same request flow. The data from the backend was normalized using a small parsing layer so that the frontend receives uniform structures regardless of the module generating the alert.</p><h3><strong>Why This Approach Was Chosen</strong></h3><p>A unified permission handler reduces uncertainty for users and simplifies long-term maintenance. Data normalization ensures adaptability, allowing new notification types to be added without rewriting large portions of the interface.</p><h3><strong>Conclusion</strong></h3><p>The frontend notification experience is now smoother, more consistent, and better aligned with backend outputs. With these fixes, users can rely on timely and clear updates across all core modules.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-17 21:20:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('9cbea9ad-777b-4177-a094-a3e678e60a9c','? Daily Work Progress Report','\"\\\"<h1>? Daily Work Progress Report</h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Shema Serge</p><p> <strong>Position:</strong> Software Developer</p><p> <strong>Date:</strong> 12 November 2025</p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I continued working on the <strong>ABY Pipeline</strong> project. My focus was on setting it up to run properly on the server and connecting it with <strong>Twilio</strong>, which allows the system to send real-time messages and updates.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>⚙️ 1. Setting Up the Pipeline on the Server</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Moved the ABY Pipeline from local development to the <strong>virtual machine (VM)</strong> server.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Checked that all configurations and services are running correctly.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Fixed small setup issues to ensure smooth startup and stability.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested to confirm that the pipeline performs the same on the server as it did locally.</li></ol><p>✅ <strong>Result:</strong> The ABY Pipeline now runs successfully on the server and is stable for use.</p><h4>? 2. Connecting Twilio for Messages</h4><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Set up <strong>Twilio integration</strong> to enable message notifications and real-time updates.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Tested message sending and receiving to confirm that communication works properly.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Verified that the connection remains stable during different system operations.</li></ol><p>✅ <strong>Result:</strong> The Twilio connection is active, allowing the system to send notifications and updates reliably.</p><h3>? Next Steps</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Continue monitoring the pipeline’s performance on the server.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Prepare documentation for the deployment setup and configuration.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Begin working on small improvements and automation features for smoother performance.</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>Today, I completed the <strong>server setup</strong> for the ABY Pipeline and successfully connected it with <strong>Twilio</strong> for real-time communication. The system is now stable, tested, and ready for use — marking a solid step forward in improving automation and message handling within ABY.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-12 20:01:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('9d3cdcce-b801-448f-8263-99dac28da4db','Barber Shop App – Folder Structure & Frontend Setup','\"\\\"<p>Today’s work focused on organizing and standardizing the folder structure of the Barber Shop application to improve scalability, maintainability, and team collaboration.</p><h3>Key Improvements</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Designed a clean and modular folder structure separating <strong>components</strong>, <strong>pages</strong>, <strong>services</strong>, <strong>hooks</strong>, and <strong>utils</strong>.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Grouped features such as <strong>appointments</strong>, <strong>staff management</strong>, <strong>services</strong>, and <strong>payments</strong> into feature-based directories.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Established shared UI components (buttons, inputs, modals) to reduce duplication and ensure design consistency.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Improved naming conventions and file organization to make onboarding easier for new developers.</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Prepared the structure to support future features like loyalty programs and analytics.</li></ol><h3>Result</h3><p>The application codebase is now easier to navigate, faster to scale, and better aligned with best practices, enabling smoother development and long-term maintainability.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-12-23 06:04:00.000','f8cab911-6027-445b-995d-a4b94efd8e00'),('9d5b898a-1ebf-4e3a-b450-dff9263a18d1','? Chat Application Real-Time Messaging & Unread Messages Report','\"\\\"<h2>? Chat Application Real-Time Messaging &amp; Unread Messages Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Honore</p><h3>? Report Overview</h3><p>I worked on improving the <strong>chat application</strong> by making the messaging system fully <strong>real-time</strong> and adding support for <strong>unread message tracking</strong>. The objective was to ensure users receive messages instantly and can easily see when they have new messages they haven’t read yet.</p><h3>?️ Work Done</h3><ol><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Implemented real-time message delivery so messages appear immediately without page refresh</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Added logic to track <strong>unread messages</strong> per conversation</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Ensured unread message indicators update correctly when new messages arrive</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\