et\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Accurate financial data available for reporting and analysis</li><li data-list=\\\\\\\"bullet\\\\\\\"><span class=\\\\\\\"ql-ui\\\\\\\" contenteditable=\\\\\\\"false\\\\\\\"></span>Backend is stable and supports all expense-related operations</li></ol><h3>? Summary</h3><p>This work strengthened the expense management module on the backend, ensuring that both expenses and credits are properly recorded, validated, and available for reporting, making the system more reliable and practical for financial management.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-21 17:37:00.000','ae4f5b82-fda2-4fb1-90fa-e94efc468605'),('c8b22981-e0b6-490e-b447-67e86e3861b9','? Aby Inventory – Client Debt Display Report','\"\\\"<h2>? Aby Inventory – Client Debt Display Report</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Ishimwe Serge</p><h3>? Overview</h3><p>I worked on the <strong>Aby Inventory system</strong> to enhance how client debt information is displayed on the frontend, specifically focusing on the <strong>stock-out process</strong>. The goal was to make outstanding client debts clearly visible to improve decision-making and reduce errors during stock-outs.</p><h3><strong>✅ Detailed Work Done</strong></h3><h4><strong>? Client Debt Display on Stock-Out</strong></h4><p>Updated the stock-out page to <strong>clearly show the client’s current debt</strong> at the moment of stock-out.</p><p> Made sure the debt information is <strong>accurate, visible, and easy to understand</strong> before finalizing the transaction.</p><p> Ensured the information dynamically reflects any previous debts and ongoing transactions.</p><h4><strong>? Frontend Workflow Improvements</strong></h4><p>Integrated the debt display smoothly into the existing stock-out workflow without disrupting other functionalities.</p><p> Enhanced clarity and user interface design so that staff can quickly identify outstanding debts while processing stock-out actions.</p>