ock supervision and provides a reflection on how the system’s backend and frontend parts are evolving. The purpose is to give a clearer picture of what has been done and what still needs attention.</p><h2><strong>Body</strong></h2><p>The stock workflow has become more structured over the past period. Items are now recorded with fewer errors thanks to improved tracking steps. Stock arrival and release routines have been refined so that each stage is documented without delays.</p><p>On the system development side, the reporting feature is shaping up well. Reports load faster, and a better layout has been created to make them easier to read. Filters for date ranges, categories, and transaction types have been added.</p><p>Backend development focused mainly on strengthening stability. Several performance bottlenecks were addressed, and redundant operations were removed. Meanwhile, the frontend now displays data more clearly, and navigation between stock views is smoother.</p><h2><strong>Conclusion</strong></h2><p>Overall progress is encouraging. The daily workflow feels more organized, and the system’s technical parts continue to improve toward full functionality. More testing will help ensure all features run consistently across different use cases.</p>\\\"\"',NULL,NULL,'2025-11-20 21:39:00.000','8f2850d4-4182-454c-bf0e-2eca4a700fc0'),('d0eb6a21-0e09-4115-a830-261d291a937b','? Daily Work Progress Report 13 November 2025','\"\\\"<h1>? Daily Work Progress Report</h1><p><strong>Name:</strong> Mihigo Prince</p><p> <strong>Position:</strong> Backend Developer</p><p> <strong>Date:</strong> 13 November 2025</p><h3>? Introduction</h3><p>Today, I worked on the <strong>Aby Booking Platform</strong>, focusing on improving the <strong>Employee Management</strong> system inside the <strong>Company Dashboard</strong>. The goal was to make it easier for partner companies to manage their staff directly through the platform.</p><h3>✅ Key Tasks Completed</h3><h4>? 1. Employee Management